        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/9–1647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simmons</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-16">September 16,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>402. Congress elected Carlos Julio Arosemena Vice President by vote 103 to 3;
                    next session scheduled 4:30 p.m. Arosemena arrives Quito this afternoon.
                    Resignation Suarez expected to be acted upon immediately and Arosemena may be
                    installed as President today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simmons</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
